# Experiment with using Tilt for local development

My dev environment
* HP Laptop (Intel Core i7, 64GB RAM, 1TB SDD)
* WSL2 w/ Docker

## Install WSL2

## Install Docker

Install the following
* kubectl - https://kubernetes.io/docs/tasks/tools/install-kubectl-linux/
* go (using PPA) - https://go.dev/wiki/Ubuntu
* kind (using go install) - https://kind.sigs.k8s.io/docs/user/quick-start/#installing-with-go-install
* ctlptl (using go install) - https://github.com/tilt-dev/ctlptl?tab=readme-ov-file#go-install

Move the commands that were installed via Go
* sudo mv $(go env GOPATH)/bin/kind /usr/local/bin/kind
* sudo mv $(go env GOPATH)/bin/ctlptl /usr/local/bin/ctlptl

Spin up a KIND cluster with a built-in registry on a pre-determined port
https://github.com/tilt-dev/ctlptl?tab=readme-ov-file#kind-with-a-built-in-registry-at-a-pre-determined-port

## Install Tilt
https://docs.tilt.dev/install.html#linux

